Michael Vick, the star quarterback for the Atlanta Falcons, faces a legal battle over federal dogfighting charges.
Co-defendant Tony Taylor pleads guilty, promising to cooperate with prosecutors.
Taylor's plea deal includes revealing details of dogfighting operations involving Vick and others.
Vick's sponsors, including Nike and Reebok, sever ties due to the scandal.
Despite the fallout, Vick's marketing future hinges on the outcome of his trial.
The indictment outlines Vick's involvement in a dogfighting ring, tarnishing his reputation.
Vick's legal troubles have led to public outrage and sponsor backlash, impacting his career and endorsements.
